This paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques for data, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of personal data and customised services, which suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB). The experimental results and validation of the approach indicate a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the challenges of preserving privacy in a fast-moving ecosystem, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the use of differential privacy suggests a connection to information theory and signal processing (cs.SI).
